<subSubSection pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,726,752]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[632,773,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Adiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[632,773,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">A. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the different coloration and coarser punctures on elytra, the sparse and minute punctures on pronotum, the widely separated superior eye-lobes and the terminal five segments of antennae almost moniliform.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
